  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Current diagnostic tools used in interstitial lung disease (ILD) do not meet the challenges
      set by the complex pathophysiology of this heterogenous group. The investigators therefore
      aimed to evaluate novel or not widely used diagnostic approaches for the detection and
      therapeutic monitoring of patients with various ILDs.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
